# X Platform - Lessons, Video System, and Advanced Streaming Security Documentation

# Project Overview

X Platform is an advanced e-learning platform designed initially for Jordanian Tawhiji students.

The platform currently focuses on Arabic and English subjects, with future support for additional educational categories and scalable course structures.

This stage introduces the complete Lessons System, Protected Video Streaming Architecture, Mux Video Integration, Signed Playback Security, DRM-Ready Architecture, Dynamic Watermark System, and advanced video protection layers.

---

# Lessons System

## Overview

The Lessons system is designed to organize educational content inside courses.

Each course can contain multiple lessons.

Lessons are displayed in a dedicated Course Lessons page that includes:

- Sidebar lesson navigation
- Secure video player
- Lesson details
- Lesson resources/files
- Video security system
- Protected access control
- Video lock integration
- Signed playback token handling
- Dynamic watermark overlay
- DRM readiness indicators

