Video Lock System
Overview

The Video Lock system prevents simultaneous video watching across devices.

Goal:

Prevent account sharing
Prevent multiple simultaneous viewers
Reduce unauthorized shared account usage
Video Lock Rules

A user:

Can watch only one video session at a time

If another device attempts playback:

Playback is blocked

The frontend displays a friendly message explaining that the account may already be watching a video on another device.

Video Lock APIs

Start video session:

POST /api/security/video/start/

Stop video session:

POST /api/security/video/stop/

Check video status:

GET /api/security/video/status/
