Signed Playback Policy

The system now requires new Mux assets to use:

signed

instead of:

public

This is important because:

Public playback IDs can be played without token protection
Signed playback IDs require a valid signed token
Direct video URL sharing becomes much harder
Playback is controlled by the backend
Important Signed Playback Note

Old videos that were created with:

public

will not work properly with signed tokens.

If an old video shows:

public

beside the playback ID in Mux, it should not be used to test signed playback.

Correct behavior requires:

signed

beside the playback ID.

