DRM Ready Architecture
Overview

The project is now prepared for future DRM activation.

DRM is not currently active because Mux requires a paid DRM access fee.

However, the codebase is ready so that when DRM becomes available, only environment values need to be added and new videos need to be uploaded.

DRM Environment Settings

The backend supports:

MUX_DRM_ENABLED=False
MUX_DRM_CONFIGURATION_ID=
MUX_DRM_SIGNING_KEY=
MUX_DRM_PRIVATE_KEY=

Current mode:

MUX_DRM_ENABLED=False

Future mode:

MUX_DRM_ENABLED=True
MUX_DRM_CONFIGURATION_ID=your_mux_drm_configuration_id
DRM Activation Flow In The Future

When DRM is purchased and enabled from Mux:

Add DRM configuration values to .env
Set:
MUX_DRM_ENABLED=True
Restart Django server
Upload new videos
New videos will be stored as DRM-protected assets
Lessons will store DRM metadata automatically
Important DRM Note

Old videos will not automatically become DRM protected.

Recommended future action:

Upload new video assets after DRM is enabled.

This ensures:

Correct DRM packaging
Correct playback configuration
Correct asset-level protection
DRM Purpose

DRM is intended to provide:

Encrypted playback
License-based video access
Hardware/browser-level protection
Screen recording blocking on supported devices
Black screen behavior during screen capture in some environments
DRM Limitations

DRM cannot be built securely from scratch using only Django and React.

True DRM depends on:

Widevine
FairPlay
PlayReady
License servers
Browser EME support
Device-level protection
Video encryption and packaging

Therefore, the platform prepares for DRM integration through Mux instead of trying to build insecure custom DRM.

