Signed Token Generation
File
courses/services/mux_signed_token.py

The system uses:

jwt.encode()

Algorithm:

RS256

Payload includes:

{
    "sub": playback_id,
    "aud": "v",
    "exp": expiration_timestamp
}

Headers include:

{
    "kid": MUX_SIGNING_KEY_ID
}
Signed Playback Security Features

Playback tokens include:

Playback ID
Expiration time
Audience validation
Signing key validation
Token Expiration

Playback tokens are temporary.

Example duration:

10 minutes

Benefits:

Reduced token reuse
Better playback security
Harder URL sharing
Short access window if token is copied
Mux Token API Response

The token endpoint now returns:

{
  "playback_id": "mux_playback_id",
  "token": "signed_playback_token",
  "expires_in_minutes": 10,
  "is_drm_protected": false,
  "drm_license_type": null,
  "watermark": {
    "username": "student_username",
    "email": "student_email",
    "device_id": "student_device_id"
  }
